        "last_activity_date": 1479504840,
        "creation_date": 1479504840,
        "body": "<p>The only way to authoritatively look up whether an entity exists is to load it by key. You can certainly do a keys-only query, but it will be eventually consistent and will not guarantee that you do not create duplicates.<\/p>\n\n<p>Given what you are trying to do, you will almost certainly be better off parenting <code>LikeMW<\/code> with the user and using the stringified likedObject as the string id. That way you can do a strongly consistent lookup and use transactions.<\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 40686273,
        "question_id": 40642828
    }],
